    "Each convolution layer contains a convolution kernel, a bias term, a ReLU activation function, and a local response normalization (LRN) module.",
    "The first convolution layer convolves the 224 × 224 × 3 input image using 96 convolution kernels of size 11 × 11 × 3 and stride 4.",
    "The second convolution layer takes the output of the first convolution layer as input and filters it with 5 × 5 × 48 kernels.",
    "The third, fourth, and fifth Fig. 18 Architecture of LeNet-5 convolution layers are connected to each other, with no pooling layer in between.",
    "The kernels of the second, fourth, and fifth convolution layers are only connected to those kernel maps of the previous convolution layer that are also located on the same GPU."
